 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align dashboard and alternate renderers with snapshot and attention sections","description":"Align the TUI dashboard and alternate renderer flows with the same snapshot and attention section model. This task exists because the dashboard should share the robot mental model rather than presenting a separate worldview that only coincidentally overlaps.","design":"The work should decide how dashboard screens, terse output, markdown output, and TOON output consume shared sections, summary metadata, and diagnostics or explainability affordances. It should explicitly preserve legitimate UI-specific affordances while preventing them from becoming a separate semantic branch, so human operators can answer why questions without diverging from machine-consumable semantics.

The result should be that snapshot and attention are conceptually recognizable everywhere.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when dashboard and alternate renderer experiences clearly reuse the shared section model and no longer depend on divergent state assembly paths.","notes":"Parity here improves operator ergonomics for both human and machine users, because it makes the product's mental model consistent.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:51:10.345346556Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T21:51:10.344708081Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dashboard","parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.434476151Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.967287453Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:12.536297631Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:36.951777963Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:44:52.669593523Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":368,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: 8.2 now waits on 7.3 because dashboard and alternate renderer parity should consume registry-backed summary metadata and drill-down hints, not invent another UI-local semantic layer. Preserve UI-specific affordances, but keep the meaning anchored in shared metadata.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:32Z"},{"id":375,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after plan-space audit: dashboard and alternate-renderer parity are a core operator experience, not a nice-to-have. Once 6.5 and 7.3 land, this should move immediately so human-facing views stop drifting from the shared robot semantics before validation freezes them.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:08:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align SSE and WebSocket behavior with durable attention semantics","description":"Align server-side streaming transports with the same durable attention semantics used elsewhere. This task exists because once attention and digest become restart-safe operator primitives, streaming transports must stop inventing their own event meanings.","design":"The work should ensure SSE and WebSocket streams honor the same cursor, replay, resync, degraded-state, request-correlation, idempotency, aggregation, cooldown, resurfacing, operator-attention-state, action-handoff, and recoverable-error semantics as CLI and REST consumers. It should also decide how stream initialization, backlog replay, and handoff to live updates behave when items are pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. This task is about semantic alignment, not merely plumbing bytes over a socket.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when streaming transports can be treated as alternative delivery mechanisms for the same durable, deduplicated, operator-shaped, and request-correlated event product rather than as bespoke feeds.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:25.318193079Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T22:04:11.598201887Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T22:04:11.597568532Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","robot-redesign","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:34.759084751Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:51.524008109Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:00.51523953