 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add benchmark and regression coverage for latency, payload size, and storage churn","description":"Add automated benchmark and regression coverage for the user-facing cost profile of the redesign. This task exists because robot mode ergonomics depend not only on semantic correctness but also on snapshot, status, digest, attention, inspect, and transport behavior staying fast, bounded, and operationally cheap as projects grow.","design":"The coverage should use the shared deterministic fixture corpus and Go testing infrastructure to measure snapshot, status, digest, attention, inspect, diagnostics, and renderer behavior under small, medium, and large scenarios plus repeated-event, retry-heavy, and operator-override-heavy scenarios. It should track payload bytes, section counts, raw event counts versus surfaced item counts where observable, truncation or pagination activation, latency, allocations, rows touched or rewritten where observable, replay throughput, diagnostic expansion cost, deduplication effectiveness, operator-state impact on surfaced queue size, and any storage-churn signals needed to verify SQLite stays operationally cheap. Use Go benchmarks and targeted regression tests rather than ad hoc shell loops. The logging should record scenario IDs, schema IDs, request IDs where relevant, render format, item counts, payload sizes, operator-state markers, suppression or resurfacing markers, diagnostic-surface depth where relevant, and enough supporting detail that a regression report explains what got slower or larger and why that matters to users.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the redesign has automated benchmark and regression coverage for latency, payload size, storage churn, compact-attention effectiveness, and operator-control overhead, with detailed logs that make regressions obvious and diagnosable. The result should prove that boundedness and performance budgets are being honored for representative scenarios rather than merely hoped for.","notes":"Fast, bounded outputs are part of the contract for agent-facing robot mode. Benchmark work should protect user experience and operational cost, not chase meaningless micro-optimizations.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:55:45.991262114Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T22:15:34.988200873Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T22:15:34.987512244Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["benchmark","performance","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:57.571500782Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:28.813873196Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:29.449135271Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:39.832167367Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:48.140664593Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:09.314787309Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:12.943189537Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:11.351998992Z","created_by":"ub